tcb_info.app_compose:
{
    "allowed_envs":[
        "TOKEN",
        "HF_TOKEN",
        "CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN",
        "DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN",
        "CERTBOT_EMAIL",
        "REDIS_PASSWORD"
    ],
    "default_gateway_domain":"dstack-base-gpu8.phala.network",
    "docker_compose_file":"version: "3.8"

x-common: &common-config
  restart: always
  logging:
    driver: "json-file"
    options:
      max-size: "100m"
      max-file: "5"
  runtime: nvidia
  environment:
    - NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=all
    - TOKEN=${TOKEN}
    - SIGNING_METHOD=ecdsa
    - REDIS_HOST=redis
    - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
    - HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=${HF_TOKEN}
  volumes:
    - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/.cache/huggingface:/root/.cache/huggingface

services:
  # --- Ingress Services (One per Domain) ---
  qwen-7b-ingress:
    image: kvin/dstack-ingress@sha256:2cc3bc50d71faa4d313084237b0f5d1d25963024f2484c7a6414aed075883cdd
    container_name: dstack-ingress-qwen-7b
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "443:443"
    environment:
      - DOMAIN=qwen2-5-7b.ai.phala.com
      - TARGET_ENDPOINT=http://haproxy:80
      - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=${CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
      - GATEWAY_DOMAIN=_.${DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN}
      - CERTBOT_EMAIL=${CERTBOT_EMAIL}
      - SET_CAA=true
    volumes:
      - /var/run/tappd.sock:/var/run/tappd.sock
      - qwen-7b-cert-data:/etc/letsencrypt
    depends_on:
      - haproxy

  qwen-vl-72b-ingress:
    image: kvin/dstack-ingress@sha256:2cc3bc50d71faa4d313084237b0f5d1d25963024f2484c7a6414aed075883cdd
    container_name: dstack-ingress-qwen-vl-72b
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "444:444"
    environment:
      - DOMAIN=qwen2-5-vl-72b.ai.phala.com
      - PORT=444
      - TARGET_ENDPOINT=http://haproxy:81
      - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=${CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
      - GATEWAY_DOMAIN=_.${DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN}
      - CERTBOT_EMAIL=${CERTBOT_EMAIL}
      - SET_CAA=true
    volumes:
      - /var/run/tappd.sock:/var/run/tappd.sock
      - qwen-vl-72b-cert-data:/etc/letsencrypt
    depends_on:
      - haproxy

  # --- Shared Services ---
  haproxy:
    image: haproxy:2.9-alpine
    container_name: haproxy
    restart: always
    environment:
      - TOKEN=${TOKEN}
    depends_on:
      - vllm-proxy
      - vllm-proxy2
    configs:
      - source: haproxy_cfg
        target: /usr/local/etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg
      - source: logrotate_cfg
        target: /etc/periodic/daily/haproxy-logrotate
        mode: 755
    logging:
      driver: "json-file"
      options: { max-size: "50m", max-file: "3" }
    command: sh -c "crond && haproxy -W -f /usr/local/etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg"

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    container_name: redis_for_cloud
    restart: always
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/redis_data:/data
    environment:
      - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
      - REDIS_MAXMEMORY=2gb
      - REDIS_MAXMEMORY_POLICY=allkeys-lru
    command: redis-server --save 20 1 --loglevel warning --requirepass "${REDIS_PASSWORD}"
    sysctls:
      - net.core.somaxconn=1024
    ulimits:
      nofile:
        soft: 65535
        hard: 65535
    security_opt:
      - no-new-privileges:true
    logging:
      driver: json-file
      options:
        max-size: "10m"
        max-file: "3"

  # --- Model Stack 1: QWEN 7B ---
  model-downloader_qwen_7b:
    image: python:3.10-slim
    container_name: model-downloader-qwen-7b
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/.cache/huggingface:/root/.cache/huggingface
    environment:
      - HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=${HF_TOKEN}
    command: >
      sh -c "pip install -U huggingface_hub[cli] && hf download
      RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic --max-workers 20"

  vllm:
    <<: *common-config
    image: vllm/vllm-openai:v0.10.2
    container_name: vllm-7b
    depends_on:
      model-downloader_qwen_7b:
        condition: service_completed_successfully
    shm_size: "10.24gb"
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent:/mnt
    environment:
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen-2.5-7b-instruct
    command: >
      --model RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic
      --served-model-name qwen/qwen-2.5-7b-instruct
      --gpu-memory-utilization 0.1 --max-num-seqs 400
      --max-model-len 32768 --disable-custom-all-reduce

  vllm-proxy:
    <<: *common-config
    image: docker.io/mondaylord/vllm-proxy@sha256:f9fa1463bc2f0df80b7c6ce48403c62f1ed9b7bc27f51be5cc07668144bd1517
    container_name: vllm-proxy
    privileged: true
    depends_on:
      - redis
    volumes:
      - /var/run/dstack.sock:/var/run/dstack.sock
    environment:
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen-2.5-7b-instruct
      - VLLM_BASE_URL=http://vllm:8000
      - SIGNING_METHOD=ecdsa
      - REDIS_HOST=redis
      - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
      - TOKEN=${TOKEN}

  cronjob:
    <<: *common-config
    image: alpine:latest
    container_name: vllm_proxy_cronjob-7b
    depends_on:
      - redis
    command: >
      sh -c 'while true; do wget -q -O- --header="Authorization: Bearer $$TOKEN" http://vllm-proxy:8000/v1/attestation/report; sleep 600; done;'

  # --- Model Stack 2: QWEN VL 72B ---
  model-downloader-qwen-vl-72b:
    image: python:3.10-slim
    container_name: model-downloader-qwen-vl-72b
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/.cache/huggingface:/root/.cache/huggingface
    environment:
      - HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=${HF_TOKEN}
    command: >
      sh -c "pip install -U huggingface_hub[cli] && hf download
      RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-VL-72B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic --max-workers 20"

  vllm2:
    <<: *common-config
    image: mondaylord/vllm-openai:v0.10.2
    container_name: vllm2
    depends_on:
      model-downloader-qwen-vl-72b:
        condition: service_completed_successfully
    shm_size: "64gb"
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent:/mnt
    environment:
      - VLLM_USE_FLASHINFER_SAMPLER=0
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen2.5-vl-72b-instruct
    command: >
      --model RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-VL-72B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic
      --served-model-name qwen/qwen2.5-vl-72b-instruct
      --gpu-memory-utilization 0.75 --max-num-seqs 50
      --max-model-len 65536 --disable-log-requests
      --enable-chunked-prefill --mm-encoder-tp-mode data
      --limit-mm-per-prompt '{"image":2,"video":0}'
      --disable-custom-all-reduce

  vllm-proxy2:
    <<: *common-config
    image: docker.io/mondaylord/vllm-proxy@sha256:f9fa1463bc2f0df80b7c6ce48403c62f1ed9b7bc27f51be5cc07668144bd1517
    container_name: vllm-proxy2
    privileged: true
    depends_on:
      - redis
    volumes:
      - /var/run/dstack.sock:/var/run/dstack.sock
    environment:
      - VLLM_BASE_URL=http://vllm2:8000
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen2.5-vl-72b-instruct
      - SIGNING_METHOD=ecdsa
      - REDIS_HOST=redis
      - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
      - TOKEN=${TOKEN}

  cronjob2:
    <<: *common-config
    image: alpine:latest
    container_name: vllm_proxy_cronjob-vl-72b
    depends_on:
      - redis
    command: >
      sh -c 'while true; do wget -q -O- --header="Authorization: Bearer $$TOKEN" http://vllm-proxy2:8000/v1/attestation/report; sleep 600; done;'

volumes:
  qwen-7b-cert-data: {}
  qwen-vl-72b-cert-data: {}

configs:
  haproxy_cfg:
    content: |
      global
          log stdout local0
          maxconn 4096
          tune.ssl.default-dh-param 2048
          log-tag haproxy
      defaults
          log     global
          mode    http
          option  dontlognull
          option  http-server-close
          option  forwardfor except 127.0.0.0/8
          option  redispatch
          retries 3
          timeout queue 600s
          timeout connect 60s
          timeout client  600s
          timeout server  600s
          timeout http-request 600s
          timeout http-keep-alive 2s
          maxconn 3000
          log-format "%ci:%cp [%t] %ft %b/%s %Tq/%Tw/%Tc/%Tr/%Ta %ST %B %CC %CS %tsc %ac/%fc/%bc/%sc/%rc %sq/%bq"

      frontend qwen7b_frontend
          bind *:80
          mode http
          acl is_stats path_beg /haproxy-stats
          use_backend stats_backend if is_stats
          acl is_metrics path /v1/metrics
          acl is_authorized hdr(Authorization) -m str "Bearer ${TOKEN}"
          http-request deny if is_metrics !is_authorized
          default_backend qwen7b_backend

      frontend qwenvl_frontend
          bind *:81
          mode http
          acl is_metrics path /v1/metrics
          acl is_authorized hdr(Authorization) -m str "Bearer ${TOKEN}"
          http-request deny if is_metrics !is_authorized
          default_backend qwenvl_backend

      backend qwen7b_backend
          mode http
          option http-keep-alive
          http-reuse safe
          balance leastconn
          http-request set-priority-class int(0) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i premium }
          http-request set-priority-class int(10) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic }
          http-request return status 429 if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic } { srv_conn(qwen7b_server) ge 100 }
          http-request set-header X-Real-IP %[src]
          http-request add-header X-Forwarded-For %[src]
          server qwen7b_server vllm-proxy:8000 check maxconn 100

      backend qwenvl_backend
          mode http
          option http-keep-alive
          http-reuse safe
          balance leastconn
          http-request set-priority-class int(0) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i premium }
          http-request set-priority-class int(10) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic }
          http-request return status 429 if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic } { srv_conn(qwenvl_server) ge 10 }
          http-request set-header X-Real-IP %[src]
          http-request add-header X-Forwarded-For %[src]
          server qwenvl_server vllm-proxy2:8000 check maxconn 10

      backend stats_backend
          stats enable
          stats uri /haproxy-stats
          stats refresh 30s
          stats show-legends
          stats show-node
          stats hide-version
          stats auth admin:admin # Change for production

  logrotate_cfg:
    content: |
      #!/bin/sh
      LOG_DIR=/var/log
      find ${LOG_DIR} -name 'haproxy*.log' -mtime +7 -delete 2>/null
      if [ -f /var/run/haproxy.pid ]; then
          kill -USR1 $(cat /var/run/haproxy.pid) 2>/null || true
      fi",
    "features":[
        "kms",
        "tproxy-net"
    ],
    "gateway_enabled":true,
    "kms_enabled":true,
    "local_key_provider_enabled":false,
    "manifest_version":2,
    "name":"qwen",
    "no_instance_id":false,
    "pre_launch_script":"
#!/bin/bash
echo "----------------------------------------------"
echo "Running Phala Cloud Pre-Launch Script v0.0.7"
echo "----------------------------------------------"
set -e

# Function: notify host

notify_host() {
    if command -v dstack-util >/dev/null 2>&1; then
        dstack-util notify-host -e "$1" -d "$2"
    else
        tdxctl notify-host -e "$1" -d "$2"
    fi
}

notify_host_hoot_info() {
    notify_host "boot.progress" "$1"
}

notify_host_hoot_error() {
    notify_host "boot.error" "$1"
}

# Function: Perform Docker cleanup
perform_cleanup() {
    echo "Pruning unused images"
    docker image prune -af
    echo "Pruning unused volumes"
    docker volume prune -f
    notify_host_hoot_info "docker cleanup completed"
}

# Function: Check Docker login status without exposing credentials
check_docker_login() {
    # Try to verify login status without exposing credentials
    if docker info 2>/dev/null | grep -q "Username"; then
        return 0
    else
        return 1
    fi
}

# Main logic starts here
echo "Starting login process..."

# Check if Docker credentials exist
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_DOCKER_USERNAME" && -n "$DSTACK_DOCKER_PASSWORD" ]]; then
    echo "Docker credentials found"
    
    # Check if already logged in
    if check_docker_login; then
        echo "Already logged in to Docker registry"
    else
        echo "Logging in to Docker registry..."
        # Login without exposing password in process list
        if [[ -n "$DSTACK_DOCKER_REGISTRY" ]]; then
            echo "$DSTACK_DOCKER_PASSWORD" | docker login -u "$DSTACK_DOCKER_USERNAME" --password-stdin "$DSTACK_DOCKER_REGISTRY"
        else
            echo "$DSTACK_DOCKER_PASSWORD" | docker login -u "$DSTACK_DOCKER_USERNAME" --password-stdin
        fi
        
        if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
            echo "Docker login successful"
        else
            echo "Docker login failed"
            notify_host_hoot_error "docker login failed"
            exit 1
        fi
    fi
# Check if AWS ECR credentials exist
elif [[ -n "$DSTACK_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID" && -n "$DSTACK_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY" && -n "$DSTACK_AWS_REGION" && -n "$DSTACK_AWS_ECR_REGISTRY" ]]; then
    echo "AWS ECR credentials found"
    
    # Check if AWS CLI is installed
    if ! command -v aws &> /dev/null; then
        notify_host_hoot_info "awscli not installed, installing..."
        echo "AWS CLI not installed, installing..."
        curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64-2.24.14.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
        echo "6ff031a26df7daebbfa3ccddc9af1450 awscliv2.zip" | md5sum -c
        if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
            echo "MD5 checksum failed"
            notify_host_hoot_error "awscli install failed"
            exit 1
        fi
        unzip awscliv2.zip &> /dev/null
        ./aws/install
        
        # Clean up installation files
        rm -rf awscliv2.zip aws
    else
        echo "AWS CLI is already installed: $(which aws)"
    fi

    # Set AWS credentials as environment variables
    export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="$DSTACK_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID"
    export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="$DSTACK_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY"
    export AWS_DEFAULT_REGION="$DSTACK_AWS_REGION"
    
    # Set session token if provided (for temporary credentials)
    if [[ -n "$DSTACK_AWS_SESSION_TOKEN" ]]; then
        echo "AWS session token found, using temporary credentials"
        export AWS_SESSION_TOKEN="$DSTACK_AWS_SESSION_TOKEN"
    fi
    
    # Test AWS credentials before attempting ECR login
    echo "Testing AWS credentials..."
    if ! aws sts get-caller-identity &> /dev/null; then
        echo "AWS credentials test failed"
        notify_host_hoot_error "Invalid AWS credentials"
        exit 1
    fi

    echo "Logging in to AWS ECR..."
    aws ecr get-login-password --region $DSTACK_AWS_REGION | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin "$DSTACK_AWS_ECR_REGISTRY"
    if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
        echo "AWS ECR login successful"
        notify_host_hoot_info "AWS ECR login successful"
    else
        echo "AWS ECR login failed"
        notify_host_hoot_error "AWS ECR login failed"
        exit 1
    fi
fi

perform_cleanup

#
# Set root password if DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD is set.
#
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD" ]]; then
    echo "root:$DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD" | chpasswd
    unset $DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD
    echo "Root password set"
fi
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_ROOT_PUBLIC_KEY" ]]; then
    mkdir -p /root/.ssh
    echo "$DSTACK_ROOT_PUBLIC_KEY" > /root/.ssh/authorized_keys
    unset $DSTACK_ROOT_PUBLIC_KEY
    echo "Root public key set"
fi


if [[ -e /var/run/dstack.sock ]]; then
    export DSTACK_APP_ID=$(curl -s --unix-socket /var/run/dstack.sock http://dstack/Info | jq -j .app_id)
else
    export DSTACK_APP_ID=$(curl -s --unix-socket /var/run/tappd.sock http://dstack/prpc/Tappd.Info | jq -j .app_id)
fi
# Check if app-compose.json has default_gateway_domain field and DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN is not set
# If true, set DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN from app-compose.json
if [[ $(jq 'has("default_gateway_domain")' app-compose.json) == "true" && -z "$DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN" ]]; then
    export DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN=$(jq -j '.default_gateway_domain' app-compose.json)
fi
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN" ]]; then
    export DSTACK_APP_DOMAIN=$DSTACK_APP_ID"."$DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN
fi

echo "----------------------------------------------"
echo "Script execution completed"
echo "----------------------------------------------"
",
    "public_logs":true,
    "public_sysinfo":true,
    "public_tcbinfo":true,
    "runner":"docker-compose",
    "secure_time":false,
    "storage_fs":"zfs",
    "tproxy_enabled":true
}

tcb_info.app_compose:
{
    "allowed_envs":[
        "TOKEN",
        "HF_TOKEN",
        "CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN",
        "DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN",
        "CERTBOT_EMAIL",
        "REDIS_PASSWORD"
    ],
    "default_gateway_domain":"dstack-base-gpu8.phala.network",
    "docker_compose_file":"version: "3.8"

x-common: &common-config
  restart: always
  logging:
    driver: "json-file"
    options:
      max-size: "100m"
      max-file: "5"
  runtime: nvidia
  environment:
    - NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=all
    - TOKEN=${TOKEN}
    - SIGNING_METHOD=ecdsa
    - REDIS_HOST=redis
    - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
    - HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=${HF_TOKEN}
  volumes:
    - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/.cache/huggingface:/root/.cache/huggingface

services:
  # --- Ingress Services (One per Domain) ---
  qwen-7b-ingress:
    image: kvin/dstack-ingress@sha256:2cc3bc50d71faa4d313084237b0f5d1d25963024f2484c7a6414aed075883cdd
    container_name: dstack-ingress-qwen-7b
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "443:443"
    environment:
      - DOMAIN=qwen2-5-7b.ai.phala.com
      - TARGET_ENDPOINT=http://haproxy:80
      - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=${CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
      - GATEWAY_DOMAIN=_.${DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN}
      - CERTBOT_EMAIL=${CERTBOT_EMAIL}
      - SET_CAA=true
    volumes:
      - /var/run/tappd.sock:/var/run/tappd.sock
      - qwen-7b-cert-data:/etc/letsencrypt
    depends_on:
      - haproxy

  qwen-vl-72b-ingress:
    image: kvin/dstack-ingress@sha256:2cc3bc50d71faa4d313084237b0f5d1d25963024f2484c7a6414aed075883cdd
    container_name: dstack-ingress-qwen-vl-72b
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "444:444"
    environment:
      - DOMAIN=qwen2-5-vl-72b.ai.phala.com
      - PORT=444
      - TARGET_ENDPOINT=http://haproxy:81
      - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=${CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
      - GATEWAY_DOMAIN=_.${DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN}
      - CERTBOT_EMAIL=${CERTBOT_EMAIL}
      - SET_CAA=true
    volumes:
      - /var/run/tappd.sock:/var/run/tappd.sock
      - qwen-vl-72b-cert-data:/etc/letsencrypt
    depends_on:
      - haproxy

  # --- Shared Services ---
  haproxy:
    image: haproxy:2.9-alpine
    container_name: haproxy
    restart: always
    environment:
      - TOKEN=${TOKEN}
    depends_on:
      - vllm-proxy
      - vllm-proxy2
    configs:
      - source: haproxy_cfg
        target: /usr/local/etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg
      - source: logrotate_cfg
        target: /etc/periodic/daily/haproxy-logrotate
        mode: 755
    logging:
      driver: "json-file"
      options: { max-size: "50m", max-file: "3" }
    command: sh -c "crond && haproxy -W -f /usr/local/etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg"

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    container_name: redis_for_cloud
    restart: always
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/redis_data:/data
    environment:
      - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
      - REDIS_MAXMEMORY=2gb
      - REDIS_MAXMEMORY_POLICY=allkeys-lru
    command: redis-server --save 20 1 --loglevel warning --requirepass "${REDIS_PASSWORD}"
    sysctls:
      - net.core.somaxconn=1024
    ulimits:
      nofile:
        soft: 65535
        hard: 65535
    security_opt:
      - no-new-privileges:true
    logging:
      driver: json-file
      options:
        max-size: "10m"
        max-file: "3"

  # --- Model Stack 1: QWEN 7B ---
  model-downloader_qwen_7b:
    image: python:3.10-slim
    container_name: model-downloader-qwen-7b
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/.cache/huggingface:/root/.cache/huggingface
    environment:
      - HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=${HF_TOKEN}
    command: >
      sh -c "pip install -U huggingface_hub[cli] && hf download
      RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic --max-workers 20"

  vllm:
    <<: *common-config
    image: vllm/vllm-openai:v0.10.2
    container_name: vllm-7b
    depends_on:
      model-downloader_qwen_7b:
        condition: service_completed_successfully
    shm_size: "10.24gb"
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent:/mnt
    environment:
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen-2.5-7b-instruct
    command: >
      --model RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic
      --served-model-name qwen/qwen-2.5-7b-instruct
      --gpu-memory-utilization 0.1 --max-num-seqs 400
      --max-model-len 32768 --disable-custom-all-reduce

  vllm-proxy:
    <<: *common-config
    image: docker.io/mondaylord/vllm-proxy@sha256:f9fa1463bc2f0df80b7c6ce48403c62f1ed9b7bc27f51be5cc07668144bd1517
    container_name: vllm-proxy
    privileged: true
    depends_on:
      - redis
    volumes:
      - /var/run/dstack.sock:/var/run/dstack.sock
    environment:
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen-2.5-7b-instruct
      - VLLM_BASE_URL=http://vllm:8000
      - SIGNING_METHOD=ecdsa
      - REDIS_HOST=redis
      - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
      - TOKEN=${TOKEN}

  cronjob:
    <<: *common-config
    image: alpine:latest
    container_name: vllm_proxy_cronjob-7b
    depends_on:
      - redis
    command: >
      sh -c 'while true; do wget -q -O- --header="Authorization: Bearer $$TOKEN" http://vllm-proxy:8000/v1/attestation/report; sleep 600; done;'

  # --- Model Stack 2: QWEN VL 72B ---
  model-downloader-qwen-vl-72b:
    image: python:3.10-slim
    container_name: model-downloader-qwen-vl-72b
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent/.cache/huggingface:/root/.cache/huggingface
    environment:
      - HUGGING_FACE_HUB_TOKEN=${HF_TOKEN}
    command: >
      sh -c "pip install -U huggingface_hub[cli] && hf download
      RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-VL-72B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic --max-workers 20"

  vllm2:
    <<: *common-config
    image: mondaylord/vllm-openai:v0.10.2
    container_name: vllm2
    depends_on:
      model-downloader-qwen-vl-72b:
        condition: service_completed_successfully
    shm_size: "64gb"
    volumes:
      - /var/volatile/dstack/persistent:/mnt
    environment:
      - VLLM_USE_FLASHINFER_SAMPLER=0
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen2.5-vl-72b-instruct
    command: >
      --model RedHatAI/Qwen2.5-VL-72B-Instruct-FP8-dynamic
      --served-model-name qwen/qwen2.5-vl-72b-instruct
      --gpu-memory-utilization 0.75 --max-num-seqs 50
      --max-model-len 65536 --disable-log-requests
      --enable-chunked-prefill --mm-encoder-tp-mode data
      --limit-mm-per-prompt '{"image":2,"video":0}'
      --disable-custom-all-reduce

  vllm-proxy2:
    <<: *common-config
    image: docker.io/mondaylord/vllm-proxy@sha256:f9fa1463bc2f0df80b7c6ce48403c62f1ed9b7bc27f51be5cc07668144bd1517
    container_name: vllm-proxy2
    privileged: true
    depends_on:
      - redis
    volumes:
      - /var/run/dstack.sock:/var/run/dstack.sock
    environment:
      - VLLM_BASE_URL=http://vllm2:8000
      - MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen2.5-vl-72b-instruct
      - SIGNING_METHOD=ecdsa
      - REDIS_HOST=redis
      - REDIS_PASSWORD=${REDIS_PASSWORD}
      - TOKEN=${TOKEN}

  cronjob2:
    <<: *common-config
    image: alpine:latest
    container_name: vllm_proxy_cronjob-vl-72b
    depends_on:
      - redis
    command: >
      sh -c 'while true; do wget -q -O- --header="Authorization: Bearer $$TOKEN" http://vllm-proxy2:8000/v1/attestation/report; sleep 600; done;'

volumes:
  qwen-7b-cert-data: {}
  qwen-vl-72b-cert-data: {}

configs:
  haproxy_cfg:
    content: |
      global
          log stdout local0
          maxconn 4096
          tune.ssl.default-dh-param 2048
          log-tag haproxy
      defaults
          log     global
          mode    http
          option  dontlognull
          option  http-server-close
          option  forwardfor except 127.0.0.0/8
          option  redispatch
          retries 3
          timeout queue 600s
          timeout connect 60s
          timeout client  600s
          timeout server  600s
          timeout http-request 600s
          timeout http-keep-alive 2s
          maxconn 3000
          log-format "%ci:%cp [%t] %ft %b/%s %Tq/%Tw/%Tc/%Tr/%Ta %ST %B %CC %CS %tsc %ac/%fc/%bc/%sc/%rc %sq/%bq"

      frontend qwen7b_frontend
          bind *:80
          mode http
          acl is_stats path_beg /haproxy-stats
          use_backend stats_backend if is_stats
          acl is_metrics path /v1/metrics
          acl is_authorized hdr(Authorization) -m str "Bearer ${TOKEN}"
          http-request deny if is_metrics !is_authorized
          default_backend qwen7b_backend

      frontend qwenvl_frontend
          bind *:81
          mode http
          acl is_metrics path /v1/metrics
          acl is_authorized hdr(Authorization) -m str "Bearer ${TOKEN}"
          http-request deny if is_metrics !is_authorized
          default_backend qwenvl_backend

      backend qwen7b_backend
          mode http
          option http-keep-alive
          http-reuse safe
          balance leastconn
          http-request set-priority-class int(0) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i premium }
          http-request set-priority-class int(10) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic }
          http-request return status 429 if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic } { srv_conn(qwen7b_server) ge 100 }
          http-request set-header X-Real-IP %[src]
          http-request add-header X-Forwarded-For %[src]
          server qwen7b_server vllm-proxy:8000 check maxconn 100

      backend qwenvl_backend
          mode http
          option http-keep-alive
          http-reuse safe
          balance leastconn
          http-request set-priority-class int(0) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i premium }
          http-request set-priority-class int(10) if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic }
          http-request return status 429 if { hdr(X-User-Tier) -i basic } { srv_conn(qwenvl_server) ge 10 }
          http-request set-header X-Real-IP %[src]
          http-request add-header X-Forwarded-For %[src]
          server qwenvl_server vllm-proxy2:8000 check maxconn 10

      backend stats_backend
          stats enable
          stats uri /haproxy-stats
          stats refresh 30s
          stats show-legends
          stats show-node
          stats hide-version
          stats auth admin:admin # Change for production

  logrotate_cfg:
    content: |
      #!/bin/sh
      LOG_DIR=/var/log
      find ${LOG_DIR} -name 'haproxy*.log' -mtime +7 -delete 2>/null
      if [ -f /var/run/haproxy.pid ]; then
          kill -USR1 $(cat /var/run/haproxy.pid) 2>/null || true
      fi",
    "features":[
        "kms",
        "tproxy-net"
    ],
    "gateway_enabled":true,
    "kms_enabled":true,
    "local_key_provider_enabled":false,
    "manifest_version":2,
    "name":"qwen",
    "no_instance_id":false,
    "pre_launch_script":"
#!/bin/bash
echo "----------------------------------------------"
echo "Running Phala Cloud Pre-Launch Script v0.0.7"
echo "----------------------------------------------"
set -e

# Function: notify host

notify_host() {
    if command -v dstack-util >/dev/null 2>&1; then
        dstack-util notify-host -e "$1" -d "$2"
    else
        tdxctl notify-host -e "$1" -d "$2"
    fi
}

notify_host_hoot_info() {
    notify_host "boot.progress" "$1"
}

notify_host_hoot_error() {
    notify_host "boot.error" "$1"
}

# Function: Perform Docker cleanup
perform_cleanup() {
    echo "Pruning unused images"
    docker image prune -af
    echo "Pruning unused volumes"
    docker volume prune -f
    notify_host_hoot_info "docker cleanup completed"
}

# Function: Check Docker login status without exposing credentials
check_docker_login() {
    # Try to verify login status without exposing credentials
    if docker info 2>/dev/null | grep -q "Username"; then
        return 0
    else
        return 1
    fi
}

# Main logic starts here
echo "Starting login process..."

# Check if Docker credentials exist
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_DOCKER_USERNAME" && -n "$DSTACK_DOCKER_PASSWORD" ]]; then
    echo "Docker credentials found"
    
    # Check if already logged in
    if check_docker_login; then
        echo "Already logged in to Docker registry"
    else
        echo "Logging in to Docker registry..."
        # Login without exposing password in process list
        if [[ -n "$DSTACK_DOCKER_REGISTRY" ]]; then
            echo "$DSTACK_DOCKER_PASSWORD" | docker login -u "$DSTACK_DOCKER_USERNAME" --password-stdin "$DSTACK_DOCKER_REGISTRY"
        else
            echo "$DSTACK_DOCKER_PASSWORD" | docker login -u "$DSTACK_DOCKER_USERNAME" --password-stdin
        fi
        
        if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
            echo "Docker login successful"
        else
            echo "Docker login failed"
            notify_host_hoot_error "docker login failed"
            exit 1
        fi
    fi
# Check if AWS ECR credentials exist
elif [[ -n "$DSTACK_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID" && -n "$DSTACK_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY" && -n "$DSTACK_AWS_REGION" && -n "$DSTACK_AWS_ECR_REGISTRY" ]]; then
    echo "AWS ECR credentials found"
    
    # Check if AWS CLI is installed
    if ! command -v aws &> /dev/null; then
        notify_host_hoot_info "awscli not installed, installing..."
        echo "AWS CLI not installed, installing..."
        curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64-2.24.14.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
        echo "6ff031a26df7daebbfa3ccddc9af1450 awscliv2.zip" | md5sum -c
        if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
            echo "MD5 checksum failed"
            notify_host_hoot_error "awscli install failed"
            exit 1
        fi
        unzip awscliv2.zip &> /dev/null
        ./aws/install
        
        # Clean up installation files
        rm -rf awscliv2.zip aws
    else
        echo "AWS CLI is already installed: $(which aws)"
    fi

    # Set AWS credentials as environment variables
    export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID="$DSTACK_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID"
    export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY="$DSTACK_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY"
    export AWS_DEFAULT_REGION="$DSTACK_AWS_REGION"
    
    # Set session token if provided (for temporary credentials)
    if [[ -n "$DSTACK_AWS_SESSION_TOKEN" ]]; then
        echo "AWS session token found, using temporary credentials"
        export AWS_SESSION_TOKEN="$DSTACK_AWS_SESSION_TOKEN"
    fi
    
    # Test AWS credentials before attempting ECR login
    echo "Testing AWS credentials..."
    if ! aws sts get-caller-identity &> /dev/null; then
        echo "AWS credentials test failed"
        notify_host_hoot_error "Invalid AWS credentials"
        exit 1
    fi

    echo "Logging in to AWS ECR..."
    aws ecr get-login-password --region $DSTACK_AWS_REGION | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin "$DSTACK_AWS_ECR_REGISTRY"
    if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
        echo "AWS ECR login successful"
        notify_host_hoot_info "AWS ECR login successful"
    else
        echo "AWS ECR login failed"
        notify_host_hoot_error "AWS ECR login failed"
        exit 1
    fi
fi

perform_cleanup

#
# Set root password if DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD is set.
#
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD" ]]; then
    echo "root:$DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD" | chpasswd
    unset $DSTACK_ROOT_PASSWORD
    echo "Root password set"
fi
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_ROOT_PUBLIC_KEY" ]]; then
    mkdir -p /root/.ssh
    echo "$DSTACK_ROOT_PUBLIC_KEY" > /root/.ssh/authorized_keys
    unset $DSTACK_ROOT_PUBLIC_KEY
    echo "Root public key set"
fi


if [[ -e /var/run/dstack.sock ]]; then
    export DSTACK_APP_ID=$(curl -s --unix-socket /var/run/dstack.sock http://dstack/Info | jq -j .app_id)
else
    export DSTACK_APP_ID=$(curl -s --unix-socket /var/run/tappd.sock http://dstack/prpc/Tappd.Info | jq -j .app_id)
fi
# Check if app-compose.json has default_gateway_domain field and DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN is not set
# If true, set DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN from app-compose.json
if [[ $(jq 'has("default_gateway_domain")' app-compose.json) == "true" && -z "$DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN" ]]; then
    export DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN=$(jq -j '.default_gateway_domain' app-compose.json)
fi
if [[ -n "$DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN" ]]; then
    export DSTACK_APP_DOMAIN=$DSTACK_APP_ID"."$DSTACK_GATEWAY_DOMAIN
fi

echo "----------------------------------------------"
echo "Script execution completed"
echo "----------------------------------------------"
",
    "public_logs":true,
    "public_sysinfo":true,
    "public_tcbinfo":true,
    "runner":"docker-compose",
    "secure_time":false,
    "storage_fs":"zfs",
    "tproxy_enabled":true
}
